      "body" : "Maintaining the manpage, IMHO, is an integral part of maintaining the utility itself.\r\nThe help2man-generated page are of abysmall quality and it seems to be an assumption that nobody will read them anyway: it's all in the util -help anyway. That's preciely what I want to change: maintain the manpage as a part of the software; make it _the_ place where the utility is documented, as expected on a UNIX system.",
